using unordered maps or switch case better in this case?
PLDM is supporting only 3 types of BIOS attributes and the attributes are constructed only once. Do you think unordered maps are more beneficial in this case?

For a small number of items, the difference in lookup performance between an unordered_map and a series of if-else statements is negligible. The overhead of hashing and bucket management in unordered_map might not offer a clear advantage over the straightforward conditional checks for just three types
Agree with Gokul, changing this to a map here seems like an Un-necessary optimization.
